Flexion and readjust - level 1⁠
⁠
At some point [no matter how good a scrummager you are], you will need to take a backward step.⁠
⁠
A player's ability to readjust back whilst maintaining a strong scrum shape is another necessary skill for all forwards to develop.⁠
⁠
The readjustment back should put you into your strongest position, so focus in particular on your knee angle to ensure it's not cramped or overextended. ⁠

Simple scrum primer: Partner scrum holds.⁠
⁠
✅ Objective: maintain a strong, braced position from your head to your toes, and not leaking pressure anywhere along the chain.⁠
⁠
🦍 Partner 1 - isometric hold in base position.⁠
🦍 Partner 2 - one hand on back of head, one hand on side of hips, applying force through both these locations. ⁠
⁠
👉🏼 Beginner level: parter 2 walking around partner 1 and applying force in different locations. ⁠
👉🏼 Advanced level: partner 2 doing pushups in this position.⁠
⁠
Give it a try and let us know how you go.⁠
⁠
